  "texts": [
    "Model training was conducted on a Windows computer equipped with two Nvidia Quadro RTX 5000 graphics processing units (GPUs), an Intel Xeon Gold 6240 central processing unit (CPU) @ 2.60 GHz The processing time measurement commenced with the perturbed image pair array and concluded with a single correction vector, encompassing cropping, image normalization, CPU-GPU memory transfers, and mean estimation.",
    "Initialization of the PyTorch model was excluded from the measurement, as it is only required once during startup.",
    "Serialized versions of the model were stored and loaded with TorchScript.",
    "The MAPFoSt implementation utilized multithreading on image patches; for instance, for a 2048 × 1536 input image and a patch size of 768 × 768, four parallel processes were spawned.",
    "All timing measurements were conducted with 2048 × 1536 images, a pixel dwell time of 200 ns and computed as the mean of 10 repetitions."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}